The speaker of the Abia State House of Assembly, Rt Hon Chinedum Orji has admonished the people to adhere strictly to preventive measures against the outbreak of Coronavirus in the state. Orji stated this in a statement made available to LEADERSHIP in Umuahia, the state capital, adding that the government has launched a strong campaign against the deadly virus. He maintained that although there had been no record of the scourge in the state, it still requires the cooperation of both the people and the government to prevent and control it. Insisting that contracting the virus is not a death sentence, he advice against self-medication and the need for people to report any health challenge even if it seems common to the nearest health facility. Orji, who explained that Covid 19 is real, avoidable and preventable, added that it can be defeated as long as people comply with directives by health workers and government guidelines against it. “On our part, we have followed the procedures put in place by the government and we are satisfied with them. It is now left for all of us to ensure we play according to the rules. LEADERSHIP recalls that the House on Monday drilled the state commissioner for Health, Dr. Joe Osuji on the steps the government had taken against the pandemic. Osuji explained that the government had established three Isolation Centres at the Federal Medical Center, Umuahia, Abia State University Teaching Hospital (ABSUTH), and the Specialist Hospital in Amachara. The Commissioner also informed the lawmakers that the state has an emergency hotline to call or report any case(s) of Corona Virus within the state, which he said is 07002242362. He assured them that with measures put in place by the government and the forthcoming ones, the state is adequately prepared to prevent and contain any unlikely outbreak of the virus in the state. 